t:bold" class=3D"sdf">reported</a></u> on it and the plan was dropped. At t=
he time, several Globes voters told me they would have refused to participa=
te=E2=80=94but, of course, as at-will employees, Penske could fire them at =
any time for not doing his bidding. <br/><br/>Basically, the company now li=
mits access to Globes voters and then charges for it wherever it can. This =
year, Penske has been launching more Globes-related events, like a sponsore=
d night-before dinner for the honorary awards and a sponsored =E2=80=9Coffi=
cial first time nominee luncheon,=E2=80=9D as the invite reads, attempting =
to take a page from the Academy=E2=80=99s
Nominees Luncheon. (Remember, the Oscars are awarded by a nonprofit arts or=
ganization comprised of the people who make and market movies. The Globes a=
re=E2=80=A6 not.)  <br/> <br/>Penske has also staged tacky new Globes-brand=
ed =E2=80=9Ccelebrations,=E2=80=9D giving the perpetually carpet-ready <b>S=
haron Stone </b>a =E2=80=9CGolden Globes Icon=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://e=
mail.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUdnV6VWx1WHRD=
